The race to build

vocabulary.definition: competing eagerly with someone in order to achieve or do something
vocabulary.example: Different countries and cities are vying for the title of having the tallest structure.

vocabulary.definition: having or showing a strong desire and determination to succeed
vocabulary.example: The Jetta Tower project is an ambitious endeavor to surpass the current record.

vocabulary.definition: in a very impressive and beautiful way
vocabulary.example: The elegant form of the skyscraper rises majestically above the city skyline.
The project is considered an unprecedented feat of engineering.

vocabulary.definition: restarted or continued after a pause or interruption
vocabulary.example: Construction has resumed after facing challenges and delays.

vocabulary.definition: very large and impressive; great in importance, extent, or size
vocabulary.example: The monumental structures in Saudi Arabia are a testament to the country's ambitions.
